<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    How observant are you?
 &HT;    By Ernest Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   LUFKIN, Texas _ During the course of a day, we all use the
telephone, sit at traffic lights, see the flag, fiddle with the
radio dial, spend money and generally do thousands of things so
routine we hardly give a thought to it.
</P>
<P>
   That is until now. Here's a quiz I received from a friend via
e-mail that tests your knowledge of everyday things. Some are easy.
Some are surprisingly difficult, and there are no trick questions.
</P>
<P>
   After taking this test, you may never look at a soup can the
same way again.
</P>
<P>
   1. On a standard traffic light, is the green on the top or
bottom?
</P>
<P>
   2. How many states are there?
</P>
<P>
   3. In which hand is the Statue of Liberty's torch?
</P>
<P>
   4. What six colors are on the classic Campbell's soup label?
</P>
<P>
   5. Does a merry-go-round turn clockwise or counterclockwise?
</P>
<P>
   6. What number on the telephone dial doesn't have any letters by
it?
</P>
<P>
   7. When you walk does your left arm swing with your right or
left leg?
</P>
<P>
   8. How many matches are in a standard pack?
</P>
<P>
   9. On the U.S. flag, is the top stripe red or white?
</P>
<P>
   10. What is the lowest number on the FM dial?
</P>
<P>
   11. Which way does water go down the drain, clockwise or
counterclockwise?
</P>
<P>
   12. Which way does a ``no smoking'' sign's slash run?
</P>
<P>
   13. How many channels on a VHF TV dial?
</P>
<P>
   14. Which side of a woman's blouse are the buttons on?
</P>
<P>
   15. Which way do fans rotate?
</P>
<P>
   16. Whose face is on a dime?
</P>
<P>
   17. How many sides does a stop sign have?
</P>
<P>
   18. Do books have even numbered pages on the right or left side?
</P>
<P>
   19. How many lug nuts are on a standard car wheel?
</P>
<P>
   20. How many sides are there on a standard pencil?
</P>
<P>
   21. Sleepy, Happy, Sneezy, Grumpy, Dopey, Doc. Who's missing?
</P>
<P>
   22. How many hot dog buns are in a standard package?
</P>
<P>
   23. On which playing card is the cardmaker's trademark?
</P>
<P>
   25. On which side of a venetian blind is the cord that adjusts
the opening between the slats?
</P>
<P>
   26. On the back of a $1 bill, what is in the center?
</P>
<P>
   27. How many curves are in a standard paper clip?
</P>
<P>
   ANSWERS
</P>
<P>
   1. Bottom; 2. 50; 3. Right; 4. Blue, red, white, yellow, black,
and gold; 5. Counterclockwise; 6. 1; 7. Left; 8. 20; 9. Red; 10.
88; 11. Counterclockwise (unless you happen to be south of the
equator); 12. Towards the bottom right; 13. 12 (there is no channel
1); 14. Left; 15. Clockwise as you look at it; 16. Franklin D.
Roosevelt; 17. 8; 18. Left; 19. 5; 20. 6; 21. Bashful; 22. 6; 23.
Ace of spades; 24. Did you notice there wasn't one?; 25. Left; 26.
ONE; 27. 3.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   Ernest Murray is managing editor of The Lufkin Daily News.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: emurray(at)coxnews.com.
</P>
