<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; `SUPER TUESDAY' POST-MORTEMS &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; AND NOW THE SCORCHED-EARTH CAMPAIGN BEGINS... &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The two candidates left standing in America's ``Super Tuesday''
primary showdown turned their guns on each other Wednesday, the
first shots in what is likely to be a scorched-earth election
campaign. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Political, Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Andrew Marshall, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Moved Wed., March 8) &QL;
