<P>
   &UR; Moved as BC-ALAS-`BOREGUSH'-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BUSH VS. GORE: WHAT A CRASHING BORE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   So at least we now know where we stand. Following the electoral
fireworks of ``Super Tuesday,'' Bill Bradley, who put the liberal
cat among the cautious pigeons, and John McCain, the Vietnam
veteran who was unafraid to call a spade a spade, are both out for
the count. The disappearance of the two outsiders is a loss for
American politics. Both provided alternatives voices that needed _
and need _ to be heard. We are now left with the old Establishment,
scarcely shaken or stirred. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (EDITORIAL) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By The Editorial Board of the Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Moved Wed., March 8) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (600 words) &QL;
</P>
