 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MCCAIN STOIC AS BLOWS RAIN DOWN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   If everything had gone according to the script, it would have
been a truly arresting venue for a Republican victory bash: a funky
design center in the hottest area for gay nightlife in Los Angeles.
But, as became increasingly clear in the closing stages of John
McCain's presidential campaign, this script did not have a happy
ending. Not only did McCain fall far short of his rival, George W.
Bush, he stumbled particularly badly in the state in which he had
hoped for his greatest popular triumph, California. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Political, Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Andrew Gumbel, The Independent of London &QL;
