<TEXT>
<P>
   Weekend Section stories from The New York Times News Service for
Friday, March 10.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FEATURES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TRUEWEST-THEATER-REVIEW (New York) _ The ``superb new revival''
of Sam Shepard's ``True West'' at the Circle in the Square.
Reviewed by Ben Brantley.
</P>
<P>
   With photo, NYT1.
</P>
<P>
   COOPER-DESIGN (New York) _ Is it too much to expect the National
Design Museum to show a little design now and then? Finally
Cooper-Hewitt has taken the plunge. With the first edition of its
National Design Triennial the museum brings us real, living design.
Not the history of design; not the sociology, anthropology,
psychology, theory, politics or economics of design. Not Good
Design, Green Design or Universal Design. Just Design, the whole
field of American Design and nothing but Design. By Herbert
Huschamp.
</P>
<P>
   With photos, NYT2,3.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOVIES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NUIT-FILM-REVIEW (New York) _ Philippe Garrel's film ``Le Vent
de la Nuit'' (``Night Wind'') with Catherine Deneuve. This
beautiful but sad-hearted movie is a high point of the Film Society
of Lincoln Center's annual ``Rendez-Vous With French Cinema''
series. Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   CONDO-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Condo Painting'': John
McNaughton, director; a documentary on the painter George Condo.
Reviewed by A.O. Scott.
</P>
<P>
   DETERRENCE-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Deterrence'': Rod Lurie,
director; with Kevin Pollak, Timothy Hutton, Sheryl Lee Ralph.
Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   MIDNIGHT-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Midnight'': Walter Salles and
Daniela Thomas, director; in Portuguese, with English subtitles,
and 12 minute short ``Cuba 15,'' Elizabeth Schub, director.
Reviewed by A.O. Scott.
</P>
<P>
   MARS-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Mission to Mars'': Brian DePalma,
director; with Gary Sinise, Don Cheadle, Tim Robbins, Jerry
O'Connell. Reviewed by Elvis Mitchell.
</P>
<P>
   GATE-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``The Ninth Gate'': Roman Polanksi,
director; with Johnny Depp, Frank Langella, Lena Olin. Reviewed by
Elvis Mitchell.
</P>
<P>
   ORPHANS-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Orphans'': Peter Mullan,
director. Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   FILMS4KIDS (Undated) _ Assessing the current cinema for children
of different ages.
</P>
<P>
   AT-THE-MOVIES (Hollywood) _ News of the silver screen. By
Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-IN-BRIEF (Undated) _ Capsule reviews by New York Times
critics.
</P>
<P>
   HOMEVIDEO (Undated) _ Short items on what's news in home video
and short reviews of what's new in home video. By Peter M. Nichols.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OTHER ENTERTAINMENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SPACEMAN-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Mr. Spaceman'' by Robert Olen
Butler (Atlantic Books). Reviewed by Michiko Kakutani.
</P>
<P>
   TV-WEEKEND (Undated) _ Anita Gates spotlights the weekend's
television fare: Sunday on ABC, ``Model Behavior.''
</P>
<P>
   THEATER-NOTES (Undated) _ News of The Great White Way. By Jesse
McKinley.
</P>
<P>
   ART-NOTES (New York) _ Art world news and notes. By Carol Vogel.
</P>
<P>
   ANTIQUES-COLUMN (New York) _ The Antiques Column. By Wendy
Moonan.
</P>
<P>
   ALBUM-OF-THE-WEEK (Undated) _ Spotlighting a new album.
</P>
