<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; MCCAIN, BRADLEY THROW IN THE TOWEL &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ John McCain and Bill Bradley bade farewell to their
presidential dreams Thursday, accepting with a tinge of bitterness
that they had taken on the political establishment and lost. But
both stood by their calls for reform and pledged to continue their
crusades. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary, Political Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Mary Dejevsky, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Moved Thurs., March 9) &QL;
</P>
