<P>
   &UR; THE MOUNTAIN WEST'S PRIMARY ANTICLIMAX &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DENVER _ The presidential primary calendar keeps rolling along.
Tomorrow (Friday) it's the turn of voters in Colorado, Utah and
Wyoming to have their say. But after this week's decisive ``Super
Tuesday,'' ``Little Friday'' _ as some have dubbed it _ might now
be ``Fizzle Friday.'' Voting turnouts are expected to be dismally
low as the electorate realizes that both party nominations have
already been locked up by George W. Bush and Al Gore. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (TIMELY for Friday, March 10!: Primaries in Colo., Utah, Wyo.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Western-State Editors: Colorado, Utah, Wyoming) &QL;
