r l BC-CALORIES-ANSWERS-COX     03-09 0749
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CALORIES-ANSWERS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    EDS: WITH FOOD-CALORIES, CALORIES-RECIPES
 &HT;    Calorie Challenge
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Do you know which of these foods has the fewest calories?
</P>
<P>
   Low-fat bran muffin
</P>
<P>
   Two-egg-white omelet, made with low-fat ricotta cheese, spinach,
1 piece whole-wheat toast with 1 teaspoon margarine spread
</P>
<P>
   Tuna salad (with oil-packed tuna) on whole wheat toast with bowl
of fresh fruit and non-fat yogurt
</P>
<P>
   Chicken and pasta salad with fat-free dressing
</P>
<P>
   Apple pie
</P>
<P>
   Non-dairy cheesecake
</P>
<P>
   Broiled salmon with lemon-butter sauce
</P>
<P>
   Broiled lean round steak, with garlic sauteed in olive
</P>
<P>
   oil
</P>
<P>
   Fast food choices:
</P>
<P>
   Quarter Pounder
</P>
<P>
   Filet-O-Fish
</P>
<P>
   From the vending machine:
</P>
<P>
   Peanut butter crackers
</P>
<P>
   Lite potato chips
</P>
<P>
   Small chocolate shake
</P>
<P>
   Strawberry sundae
</P>
<P>
   Did you guess which foods in our Calorie Challenge? Here are the
answers:
</P>
<P>
   A low-fat bran muffin from Dunkin' Donuts has 240 calories, 4
grams of protein, 57 grams carbohydrates, 1 gram fat.
</P>
<P>
   A two-egg-white omelet, made with low-fat ricotta cheese,
spinach, one piece of whole-wheat toast with 1 teaspoon margarine
spread has 162 calories, 33 grams protein, 10 grams carbohydrates,
6.3 grams fat.
</P>
<P>
   Verdict: More is less: Eat the omelet, and all its trappings.
Not only will you be satisfied longer, but you're taking in half
the calories for much more food.
</P>
<P>
   Splurge if you want, and add a whole egg; you can still afford
the calories and nutrition.
</P>
<P>
   A tuna salad made with oil-packed tuna on whole wheat toast with
a bowl of fresh fruit and non-fat yogurt has 699 calories and 19
grams of fat.
</P>
<P>
   Chicken and pasta salad with fat-free dressing has
</P>
<P>
   395 calories and 9.7 grams fat.
</P>
<P>
   Verdict: We like to think of tuna as a diet food, and pasta as
anti-diet. But it's not the case when the tuna is oil-packed and
combined with mayonnaise. In this case, calories from fat outweigh
the nutrients in the fruit and yogurt.
</P>
<P>
   Broiled salmon with lemon-butter sauce has 375 calories and 37.8
grams fat (9.3 saturated).
</P>
<P>
   Broiled lean round steak with garlic sauteed in olive oil has
379 calories, 38 grams fat (4.7 saturated).
</P>
<P>
   Verdict: Salmon's another food we think of as healthful, but it
compares greatly to lean steak in fat as well as calories. Salmon
is neither fat-free, nor saturated fat-free. The butter pushes the
saturated fat of the salmon meal over the top. Moral: Enjoying a
lean steak can't hurt once in a while.
</P>
<P>
   Apple pie has 210 calories, 29 grams carbohydrates, 9 grams fat.
</P>
<P>
   Non-dairy cheesecake has 160 calories, 16 grams carbohydrates,
10 grams fat.
</P>
<P>
   Verdict: Bet you thought apple pie was a safe bet next to
cheesecake. But cheesecake made with tofu, which has won numerous
taste awards, wins out. Even though it has 1 gram more fat, it has
far less sugar and calories than the apple pie. The cheesecake
offers vegetable protein as well.
</P>
<P>
   Peanut butter crackers have 138 calories, 3 grams protein, 6.6
grams fat, 16 grams carbohydrates.
</P>
<P>
   Lite potato chips have 133.5 calories, 2 grams protein, 5.8
grams fat, 18.9 grams carbohydrates.
</P>
<P>
   Verdict: Looks like the peanut butter crackers would lose out,
but they have more protein and less sugar. That gives them more
punch for the numbers and more staying power as well. You won't
have to eat ``just one more'' to be satisfied.
</P>
<P>
   A Quarter Pounder has 430 calories, 21 grams fat, 23 grams
protein, 27 grams carbohydrates.
</P>
<P>
   A Filet-O-Fish has 470 calories, 26 grams fat, 15 grams protein,
45 grams carbohydrates.
</P>
<P>
   Verdict: Both of these are very high calorie foods, and both
contain huge amounts of fat, but the fish falls short in protein,
and has more sugar (carbohydrates). Beef wins.
</P>
<P>
   A small chocolate shake has 360 calories, 9 grams fat, 60 grams
carbohydrates, 11 grams protein.
</P>
<P>
   A strawberry sundae has 290 calories, 7 grams fat, 50 grams
carbohydrates, 7 grams protein.
</P>
<P>
   Verdict: Both these items are high in sugar, of course, but the
calories can't be ignored in the shake, even though it has more
protein. One note: Combine these numbers with the numbers in the
Quarter Pounder, and you can see how one trip to the fast-food
window can kill a diet in a hurry.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
