<TEXT>
<P>
   The  &UR; New York Times News Service &LR;  is planning an expanded
weather package, with a planned starting date of Monday, March 20.
The package, consisting of a weather map as a graphics file and a
text file to accompany the map, is available to graphics clients of
the News Service.
</P>
<P>
   The new map grows to 4 columns in width (52 picas), from 3, and
is 6 inches deep; the old was 4\ inches deep. This new size permits
the insertion of cloud cover information and the addition of many
new cities (see list below).
</P>
<P>
   The map is available both in color and in black and white. The
colors on the new map remain the same as those on the old.
</P>
<P>
   A sample of the new map is available at Weick, Newscom,
Presslink and AP's GraphicsNet.
</P>
<P>
   A summary of this information is included in each day's Graphics
Budget.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions, contact
</P>
<P>
   Sergio Florez
</P>
<P>
   Deputy Director for Photos and Graphics New York Times News
Service
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (212) 556-4204
</P>
<P>
   FAX: (212) 556-3535
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: florez(at)nytimes.com
</P>
