<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-09 17:50 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2059 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f BC-HOMEDEPOT-LATAM10-COX     03-09 0296
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOMEDEPOT-LATAM10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Latin America, Europe may be part of Home Depot's expansion
plans
 &HT;    By Patti Bond
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Home Depot is on the verge of announcing more details
about its international expansion, an analyst said.
</P>
<P>
   The news may include one of several possibilities in Latin
America or Europe, said Wayne Hood of Prudential Securities. The
Atlanta-based home improvement retailer has been talking with
Wal-Mart Stores about acquiring Sam's Club sites in Argentina for
its previously announced expansion in Buenos Aires, Hood said. Home
Depot reportedly is looking to buy at least three Sam's Clubs for
about $50 million.
</P>
<P>
   Neither Home Depot nor Wal-Mart would comment on a possible
deal.
</P>
<P>
   The acquisition would help Home Depot meet its goal to open four
or five stores this year in Argentina. The retailer has four stores
in Chile.
</P>
<P>
   Another possible announcement could confirm speculation that
Home Depot is lining up an entry into Europe, Hood said. British
newspapers have been reporting recently that Home Depot is eyeing
acquisitions in the United Kingdom, but Hood is looking elsewhere
on the map.
</P>
<P>
   ``We would not be surprised if the company were to announce its
intention to move into Germany,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Speculation about Home Depot's European interests picked up last
March when the retailer hired Ikea President Anders Moberg to lead
its international business. Moberg significantly expanded the
Swedish furniture chain throughout Europe and the Asia-Pacific
region.
</P>
<P>
   Hood rates Home Depot's shares a ``hold.'' The retailer's stock
rose more than 5 percent Thursday, closing at $55.31 1/4, up $2.93
3/4.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
