<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   MCCAIN _ Coverage of Sen. John McCain's noon news conference and
the announcement that he is suspending his bid for the GOP
nomination. (Sherman, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   w/MCCAIN-ANALYSIS _ Post-mortem on the McCain campaign, looking
at what went wrong and what kind of legacy his insurgent campaign
may have. (Sherman, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY-QUITS _ Coverage of Sen. Bill Bradley's withdrawal from
the race for the Democratic nomination. (Foskett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   FLA-PRIMARY _ TALLAHASSEE, Fla. _ John McCain may have been
captured by the forces of George W. Bush but the former Marine
general leading his Florida campaign is urging his troops to storm
the polls Tuesday and vote for McCain. ``We stilll have something
to say,'' said Bob Milligan, state comptroller and McCain's Florida
campaign director. ``Our votes still count and we want to make sure
that John McCain's voice is still heard.'' (Crowley, Palm Beach
Post)
</P>
<P>
   POL-TICKER _ A brief roundup of the day's campaign events,
pulled from Cox staff and wire reports. (Cox News Service) MOVED..
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   CUBA-ELIAN _ MIAMI _ After more than three months of protests
both here and in Cuba, and congressional hearings, the case of
6-year-old Elian Gonzalez comes before a federal judge Thursday
weighing key questions in the international custody dispute. U.S.
District Judge K. Michael Moore is being asked to decide whether
one of Elian's great-uncles can legally challenge a U.S.
Immigration and Naturalization Service ruling that Elian be
returned to his father in Cuba. The lawsuit filed by Lazaro
Gonzalez also seeks a political asylum hearing for the boy. A
hearing on the suit was to begin Thursday. Developing. (MWilliams,
Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (i) International and (w) Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   CUBA-ELIAN _ MIAMI _ After more than three months of protests
both here and in Cuba, and congressional hearings, the case of
6-year-old Elian Gonzalez comes before a federal judge Thursday
weighing key questions in the international custody dispute. U.S.
District Judge K. Michael Moore is being asked to decide whether
one of Elian's great-uncles can legally challenge a U.S.
Immigration and Naturalization Service ruling that Elian be
returned to his father in Cuba. The lawsuit filed by Lazaro
Gonzalez also seeks a political asylum hearing for the boy. A
hearing on the suit was to begin Thursday. Developing. (MWilliams,
Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (i) International and (w) Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   DISASTER-AID _ WASHINGTON _ With the mayor of Princeville, N.C.,
and the local Congress member looking on, a House committee
Thursday restored funds for a $1.5 million study on raising a dike
that protects the largely black town. The funds had been dropped
from a package of $347 million in emergency aid to victims of
Hurricane Floyd. (Moscoso, Cox News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   IRS-AUDITS _ WASHINGTON _ Some 20 conservative groups who have
criticized the Clinton adminstration have wound up audited by the
Internal Revenue Service. Are politicians using the tax service to
punish enemies? More than three years since that Watergate-era
question made a comeback, neither Congress, the IRS nor the courts
have provided a comprehensive answer. Now aides on Capitol Hill say
an almost forgotten probe begun in 1997 will yield a report in the
``next few weeks.'' (Malone, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   MEDICARE-WELLNESS _ WASHINGTON _ A bipartisan, bicameral group
of lawmakers unveil a Medicare proposal designed to move the
program toward enhanced preventive coverage. (Lipman, Cox News
Service). 12.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-VISAS _ WASHINGTON _ After a partisan battle, the Senate
Judiciary Committee on Thursday approved a bill to sharply increase
the number of H-1B visas for high-skilled immigrants. (Schultz, Cox
News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   NATION
</P>
<P>
   LEWIS-CLOTHES _ ATLANTA _ The clothes worn by Baltimore Ravens'
All-Pro linebacker Ray Lewis after the Super Bowl when two people
wre slain outside an Atlanta nightspot have turned over to
prosecutors by Jessica Robertson, part of her deal to avoid
prosecution. Her attorney tells us the story, on the record.
(Rankin, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
