airlines what to do. The Federal Aviation Administration will
consult with the airlines every two hours, and the government will
also open up military airspace off the East Coast, try to route
more planes over Canada and use a new computer system to get hourly
updates on how many planes the airlines want to fly. By Matthew L.
Wald.
