New York's Republican presidential primary system ``absolute
nonsense,'' Joseph L. Bruno, the Republican leader of the State
Senate, called Thursday for top-to-bottom reform, making ballots
easier to understand, and making it simpler for candidates to get
on the ballot. Voters said they had difficulty understanding the
Republican primary ballot, which showed delegates' names in large
type, with the names of the presidential candidates those delegates
supported listed below, in much smaller print. (Steve Berman/The
New York Times)
