<P>
   (NYT37) LARCHMONT, N.Y. -- March 9, 2000 -- SUBURBAN-NANNIES --
The first real stirrings of spring signal another ritual for the
nannies of the suburbs, who are all but invisible from Thanksgiving
to Easter. In balmy weather, they flock to parks and playgrounds,
renewing old friendships and making new ones. In Turtle Park on
Thursday, nannies and their charges were out in full force. (James
Estrin/The New York Times)
</P>
