negative news about Sotheby's and Christie's since the federal
antitrust investigation heated up last month has left many
wondering what these auction houses will have to sell at their
important spring sales. So Christie's was eager to send out the
word that one of the stars of its sale of Impressionist and
Post-Impressionist works on May 8 will be what it calls the most
important Caillebotte ever to reach the auction block: ``Man on the
Balcony, Boulevard Haussmann'' (1880). (Christie's/The New York
Times)
