daguerreotype images he made of her for his exhibiton at
Pace/MacGill. ``I have always attempted to create images that
deliver the maximum amount of information about the subject,'' said
Close. ``I was fascinated by the clarity and detail of the
daguerreotype. Nothing gets lost.'' (Sara Krulwich/The New York
