Spagnoli's Chelsea studio. In Spagnoli's opinion, a daguerreotype
is not a photograph at all but an ``optical system'' involving the
plate, the viewer and light. ``The closer you get to a
daguerreotype, the more you see,'' said Spagnoli. ``In some ways
it's the opposite of a painting, which breaks down into brush
strokes.'' (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times) *LITE
