<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-09 22:40 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2353 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s BC-BKC-GATECH-FSU10-COX     03-09 0425
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-GATECH-FSU10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    FSU ends Cremins era
 &HT;    By J.C. Clemons
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHARLOTTE, N.C. _ When it was all said and done, there was
little left to say about the Bobby Cremins Era at Georgia Tech.
Other than it is indeed over.
</P>
<P>
   Florida State defeated the Yellow Jackets 63-62 Thursday night
in the opening game of the ACC Tournament, ending Tech's season at
13-17, and finishing Cremins' 19-year stint.
</P>
<P>
   For a night, the Charlotte Coliseum became ``Bobby's House,''
with the crowd cheering on the likeable coach.
</P>
<P>
   But Cremins' last dance started out more as a tumbling two-step
than a smooth waltz before the Yellow Jackets made an inspired
charge that was more frantic than fantastic.
</P>
<P>
   Playing a full-court, trapping defense in the second half for
one of the few times all season, Tech began to chip away at a
nine-point FSU lead.
</P>
<P>
   Alvin Jones slammed home a spinning, two-handed dunk, and the
Jackets were 53-52 with 3 minutes, 24 seconds left.
</P>
<P>
   Shaun Fein's 3-pointer got Tech's deficit to 59-57, and after a
shot-clock violation against the 'Noles at :30.4, the Jackets had
the ball _ and a chance.
</P>
<P>
   It slipped away.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Collier's's hook from the left block went awry, and FSU
took possession after Tech knocked the ball out of bounds. FSU made
four of four free throws to move on.
</P>
<P>
   Collier, a senior, had 19 points in his final game at Tech.
</P>
<P>
   Early on, the Jackets tossed up 3-point attempts with wild
abandon, while 7-foot Collier and 6-foot-11 Jones got few touches.
</P>
<P>
   Six of Tech's first 11 field-goal attempts were from beyond
3-point range, but they made only one and fell down to the
Seminoles 11-4. Yet, FSU wasn't feeling it from outside, either.
</P>
<P>
   A 13-4 Tech run, fueled by five Seminoles turnovers, got the
Bobby backers into the game, and T.J. Vines fed Fein on a breakaway
layup that put the Jackets ahead 17-15.
</P>
<P>
   However, the Jackets would score only eight points over the
final 7:22 of the first half, and trailed 25-23 at intermission.
</P>
<P>
   During the first 20 minutes, Tech made only 30 percent of its
field-goal tries, and was four of 15 from long range. Tony Akins
and Jason Floyd were a combined three of 11 on 3-point attempts.
Worse than that, though, was a five of 16 free-throw line showing.
</P>
<P>
   Collier, who led the Jackets in regular-season scoring (16.5
ppg.), managed only four points and had as many turnovers (3) as
field-goal tries in the first half.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
