<HEADLINE>
HULL GETTING CHANCE TO REST HIS AILING HIP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEFF CAPLAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Dallas Stars coach Ken Hitchcock said Brett
Hull's nagging hip flexor continues to rob him of the ability to
accelerate, and that it's time to allow the injury a chance to heal
before the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The Stars will hold Hull out of games and practice for three or
four days, including Friday night's game against the New York
Islanders, Hitchcock said. Hitchcock said Hull will be evaluated
Saturday and might play Sunday against his former team, the Western
Conference-leading St. Louis Blues.
</P>
<P>
   ``He has to get better,'' Hitchcock said. ``He's not able to
push off with any acceleration. It's just too weak.''
</P>
<P>
   Hull, who is on a strenuous exercise program off the ice, scored
his 20th goal of the season and the 606th of his career on
Wednesday. The goal marked the 13th consecutive season that Hull
has scored at least 20 goals, although he is on pace to have his
lowest-scoring season since he was a rookie in 1986-87. HATCHER
DOUBTFUL
</P>
<P>
   Nine games into his return from a lacerated calf muscle, captain
Derian Hatcher is doubtful for Friday night's game with a sore
Achilles' tendon. He played Wednesday with the flu, but left the
game in the third period with the injury.
</P>
<P>
   He had a magnetic-resonance-imaging exam Thursday, and the Stars
expect the results Friday. Hatcher missed nine weeks before
returning Feb. 18. SYDOR UP FRONT
</P>
<P>
   Defenseman Darryl Sydor played on the wing Wednesday because so
many forwards were injured. After Derian Hatcher left the game,
Sydor moved back to defense.
</P>
<P>
   Ken Hitchcock said Sydor will play up front Friday on the power
play and might see time as a winger depending on Hatcher's status.
BRIEFLY
</P>
<P>
   _ Jon Sim, recalled from the Michigan K-Wings on Tuesday, scored
his fourth goal of the season for the Stars on Wednesday in his
third stint with the team. Sim was recalled Feb. 25 and was in
uniform for four games, but did not play before being sent back to
Kalamazoo, Mich. ``I'm just waiting for my chance to play,'' Sim
said. ``I want to make the most of it every night.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Ken Hitchcock will not visit the White House on March 16 with
the rest of the team to celebrate their Stanley Cup championship
because of a scheduling conflict. Hitchcock plays host to the
Family Gateway Golf Tournament, a charity event, on that day. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
